title: Discover Washington, D.C.
content: The best way to get a real appreciation for the history, the people, and the vision that have shaped our country is  a trip to the source. As our nation’s capital, this city brims with beautiful monuments, commemorative statues and memorials, and impressive national government centers, like the Capitol Building itself. Students of all ages flock to this special city for a face-to-face experience with our heritage. They come away with expanded appreciation and the memories of a lifetime.

title: Lacrosse Tours
content:
Excel Sports is a leader in organizing international trips to Europe, from friendly matches to highly competitive games. Men’s and women’s teams, college and youth programs can all benefit from our customized packages specifically designed for your lacrosse team. Excel Sports has the contacts to arrange games against prestigious private schools and universities in the UK and elsewhere so you can experience both great lacrosse and fascinating sightseeing.

title: Theatre Performing Opportunities
content:
When we think about a stage, we think about all of the players – cast, crew, writers, directors, audience – coming together to make a moment that is living right now. And that moment grows into a memory that has a life of its own – alive in the players that were all a part of it.

This is what our theatre performing opportunities are designed to create. It’s why we take you to new stages in epic places around the world – so you can be part of new, different moments that will endure. Moments that remind us how we got here and foretell where we’ll go.

title: Dance and Cheer Programs
content:
The stage is set. Your spotlight’s waiting.

Our popular dance and cheer programs give dancers and cheerleaders the chance to learn from star-quality professionals at high-exposure venues – like bowl games and national parades. Our dance and cheer travel programs give students one-on-one access to top-notch choreographers. No matter which you choose, your students will stretch, grow, and have some fun – under the lights and with friends in a fabulous new city. Our event choreographers are top names in the business, and they work with all skill levels. Come dance with Mandy Moore, Bonnie Story, or Travis Wall, to name a few!

title: Other Professional Programs
content:
In academic disciplines like law, engineering, medicine, education, and journalism, today’s students apply what they learn in a real world context. And that real world doesn’t end at the nation’s border.

Do you imagine education students exploring international standards? Nursing students working in a clinic in Central America?  Engineers meeting with the team constructing a skyscraper in a booming Asian capital? Our customized programs provide professional interactions that can help students in career-focused disciplines shape their future. Work with our Global Academic Team to craft a professional program that suits your curriculum. Before you start, explore our popular destinations to find the one that will inspire students in your field.

title: Pre-Matriculation Adventure Programs
content: Build excitement and community among your new cohort with travel programs to kick-off the full-time MBA or law school experience. For many universities, the pre-matriculation program has become integral to the class identity, bonding, and networking of students. Oftentimes, second-year students will serve as Program Leaders, working with WorldStrides to plan the logistics of the programs and recruit first-year students during the admissions process. We are proud to support these pre-matriculation adventure programs in destinations around the world, providing non-traditional networking opportunities for students outside the classroom.
